   <conbody>
      <hazardstatement conref="../../Library/Warnings_Library_0000325173.dita#war_lib/bypass-turn-off-output-loss"
                       otherprops="3pMBS"
                       platform="PxW WxW"
                       class="+ topic/note hazard-d/hazardstatement ">
         <messagepanel class="+ topic/ul hazard-d/messagepanel ">
            <typeofhazard class="+ topic/li hazard-d/typeofhazard "/>
            <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid "/>
         </messagepanel>
      </hazardstatement>
      <hazardstatement otherprops="2pMBS"
                       type="notice"
                       class="+ topic/note hazard-d/hazardstatement ">
         <messagepanel class="+ topic/ul hazard-d/messagepanel ">
            <typeofhazard class="+ topic/li hazard-d/typeofhazard ">loss of output voltage</typeofhazard>
            <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid ">When the manual bypass switch is in <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Bypass</b> position, <ph platform="PxW" class="- topic/ph ">there is no backup from the battery</ph>
               <ph platform="WxW" class="- topic/ph ">it is not possible for the system to automatically
switch back to inverter operation</ph> in case the bypass mains becomes
unavailable.</howtoavoid>
         </messagepanel>
      </hazardstatement>
      <p class="- topic/p ">This function check describes how to perform a basic function check
on a single system or one unit in a system with multiple units.</p>
      <ol class="- topic/ol ">
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the system is in <ph platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/ph ">normal operation</ph>
               <ph platform="SDC" class="- topic/ph ">float charge</ph> and that no alarms are active.</p>
         </li>
         <li platform="PxW SDC" class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Open the rectifier mains input breaker.</p>
         </li>
         <li platform="PxW SDC" class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the system switches to battery
operation and that the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Batt. operation
time ...min</codeph>.</p>
            <note class="- topic/note ">The remaining runtime will only be
shown if advanced battery monitor is installed.</note>
         </li>
         <li platform="PxW" class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Open the battery breaker.</p>
         </li>
         <li platform="WxW" class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Open the inverter input switch.</p>
         </li>
         <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the system switches to bypass
operation and that the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Bypass operation</codeph>.</p>
         </li>
         <li platform="PxW SDC" class="- topic/li ">Close the rectifier mains input breaker.</li>
         <li platform="WxW" class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Keep the charging/discharging switch in position
2 to charge the DC capacitors <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(CB02)</b>. Keep the switch in position
2 until the warning LED turns off. With the switch still in position
2 close the inverter input switch.</p>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the system switches to <ph platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/ph ">normal
operation</ph>
               <ph platform="SDC" class="- topic/ph ">float charge</ph> and that the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph platform="PxW WxW" class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Normal operation load
power ...%</codeph>
               <codeph platform="SDC" class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Float charge load ...%</codeph>.</p>
         </li>
         <li platform="PxW" class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Close the battery breaker.</p>
         </li>
         <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Switch to bypass operation:</p>
            <ol conref="Bruce_How_to_Switch_from_Normal_Operation_to_Bypass_Operation_CPT_0000916381.dita#HowToSwitchFromNormalOperationToByp-74A61565/BP_Switch-to-bypass"
                class="- topic/ol ">
               <li class="- topic/li "/>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the white static switch EN LED
is active on the mimic diagram and that the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Bypass operation</codeph>.</p>
         </li>
         <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Switch to manual bypass and turn the system
off and on:</p>
            <ol class="- topic/ol ">
               <li otherprops="generalM 3pMBS" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Turn the manual bypass switch to
the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Test</b> position. </p>
               </li>
               <li otherprops="2pMBS" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Turn the manual bypass switch to the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Bypass</b> position.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Manual bypass on</b> LED is active on the
alarm panel and that the white manual bypass LED is active on the
mimic diagram.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Turn off the system, press both the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">ON button</b> and the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">OFF button</b> for two seconds. The <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph platform="PxW" class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Standby</codeph>
                     <codeph platform="WxW" class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Charger only</codeph>
                     <ph platform="WxW" class="- topic/ph "> (Standby)</ph>.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Measure the output voltage.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Turn on the system, press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">ON button</b> for one second.
After a few seconds the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Normal operation
load power ...%</codeph>.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Switch to bypass operation:</p>
                  <ol conref="Bruce_How_to_Switch_from_Normal_Operation_to_Bypass_Operation_CPT_0000916381.dita#HowToSwitchFromNormalOperationToByp-74A61565/BP_Switch-to-bypass"
                      class="- topic/ol ">
                     <li class="- topic/li "/>
                  </ol>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">The <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Bypass operation</codeph>.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Turn the manual bypass switch to the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Normal</b> position.</p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Switch to normal operation:</p>
            <ol conref="Bruce_How_to_Switch_from_Bypass_Operation_to_Normal_Operation_CPT_0000916380.dita#HowToSwitchFromBypassOperationToNor-74A64CEF/BP_Switch-to-normal"
                class="- topic/ol ">
               <li class="- topic/li "/>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">The <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Normal
operation load power ...%</codeph>.</p>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Reset any alarms by pressing the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">C key</b> twice.</p>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Make sure the system operates correctly and no alarms are present.</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
